美洲假吸血蝠為[[新大陸|新大陸]]上最大型的蝙蝠，同時也是世界上最大行的肉食性蝙蝠<ref name="Nuwer 2016">{{cite web| url=https://www.smithsonianmag.com/science-nature/worlds-carnivorous-bats-are-emerging-dark-180959042/| title=The World’s Carnivorous Bats Are Emerging From the Dark| last=Nuwer| first=Rachel| date=10 May 2016| website=Smithsonian.com| publisher=Smithsonian Institution| access-date=17 July 2017| archive-date=2018-07-18| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180718030636/https://www.smithsonianmag.com/science-nature/worlds-carnivorous-bats-are-emerging-dark-180959042/| dead-url=no}}</ref>。翼展可達 {{convert|0.7-1.0|m|ft|abbr=on}}<ref name="Navarro 1982">{{cite journal| doi=10.2307/3503798| url=http://www.bio-nica.info/Mammalia/Vampirum_spectrum.pdf| jstor=3503798| title=''Vampyrum spectrum''| journal=Mammalian Species| issue=184| pages=1| year=1982| last1=L.| first=Daniel Navarro| last2=Wilson| first2=Don E| access-date=2019-01-08| archive-date=2017-10-01| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171001130856/http://www.bio-nica.info/Mammalia/Vampirum_spectrum.pdf| dead-url=no}}</ref> 
，[[前臂|前臂]]長度為 {{cvt|101-110|mm|in}}<ref name="Gardner 2008">{{cite book| last=Gardner| first=A. L.| year=2008| publisher=University of Chicago Press| volume=1| title=Mammals of South America, Volume 1: Marsupials, Xenarthrans, Shrews, and Bats|page=299–300| isbn=978-0226282428| url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dbU3d7EUCm8C}}</ref>，拇指長 {{cvt|21.4-22.2|mm|in}}<ref name="Silva 2011">{{cite journal|last1=da Silva| first1= A. P.| last2= Rossi| first2= R. V.| year= 2011| title= New records of ''Vampyrum spectrum'' (Chiroptera, Phyllostomidae) for the Pantanal domain in Brazil, with notes on the species natural history, biometry, and lower incisors arrangement| journal= Chiroptera Neotropical| volume= 17| issue=1| pages= 836–841}}</ref>，上面具有類似[[貓|貓]]的彎曲利爪<ref name="Navarro 1982"/>。全身體長可達 {{convert|135–147|mm|in|abbr=on}}，體重約為 {{convert|134-189|g|oz|abbr=on}}<ref name="Simmons 1998">{{cite journal| last1= Simmons| first1= N. B.| last2= Voss| first2= R. S.| year= 1998| title= The mammals of Paracou, French Guiana, a Neotropical lowland rainforest fauna. Part 1, Bats| journal= Bulletin of the AMNH| issue= 237| url= http://digitallibrary.amnh.org/handle/2246/1634| access-date= 2019-01-08| archive-date= 2019-01-11| archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20190111132409/http://digitallibrary.amnh.org/handle/2246/1634| dead-url= no}}</ref><ref name="Silva 2011"/>。

總體來說，美洲假吸血蝠的頭顱骨類似於縮小版的[[犬科|犬科]]或[[熊科|熊科]]頭顱骨<ref name="Sharlene 2016">{{cite journal|doi=10.1098/rspb.2016.0615|pmid=27170718|pmc=4874722|title=Go big or go fish: Morphological specializations in carnivorous bats|journal=Proceedings of the Royal Society B: Biological Sciences|volume=283|issue=1830|pages=20160615|year=2016|last1=Santana|first1=Sharlene E|last2=Cheung|first2=Elena}}</ref>

美洲假吸血蝠的腦相對於身體來說偏大（1:67），其{{link-en|腦部身體質量比|brain-to-body mass ratio}}甚至較貓狗還高<ref name="Bhatnagar 2016">{{cite journal|doi=10.1002/ar.23321|pmid=26800031|title=The Chiropteran Brain Database: Volumetric Survey of the Hypophysis in 165 Species|journal=The Anatomical Record|volume=299|issue=4|pages=492–510|year=2016|last1=Bhatnagar|first1=Kunwar P|last2=Smith|first2=Timothy D|last3=Rai|first3=Shesh N|last4=Frahm|first4=Heiko D}}</ref><ref name="brain size">{{cite web| url=http://serendipstudio.org/exchange/brains/intelligence/size| title=Measuring Brain Size versus Body Size| website=Serendip Studio| publisher=Serendip| access-date=24 July 2018| archive-date=2018-10-19| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181019155912/https://serendipstudio.org/exchange/brains/intelligence/size| dead-url=no}}</ref>。

